## Governance

### Three Laws
<!-- REQUIRED: These are non-negotiable -->
1. No remediation without a Work Order
2. No Work Order without an evidence-backed finding
3. No finding without investigation

### Quality Gates

<!-- ADAPT: Agent lists active phases from quality-gate-manifest.json -->

```bash
# Before every commit
bash scripts/gate-runner.sh pre_commit --continue-on-failure

# After completing a Work Order
bash scripts/gate-runner.sh wo_exit --continue-on-failure

# Comprehensive audit
bash scripts/gate-runner.sh full_audit --continue-on-failure
```

### Quality Gates (source of truth: `.claude/quality-gate-manifest.json`)

<!-- ADAPT: Agent lists gates per phase from manifest -->

### Zero-Stub Policy
<!-- REQUIRED -->
No `NotImplementedError`, no `pass`-only functions, no `# TODO` in committed code. If it can't be implemented fully, flag it as a blocker.

## Development Workflow

<!-- ADAPT: Agent generates from language/framework/package manager -->

```bash
# <!-- EXAMPLE: Python -->
python -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -e ".[dev]"
pre-commit install

# <!-- EXAMPLE: TypeScript -->
# npm install
# npm run build
# npm test
```

## Work Order Protocol

<!-- REQUIRED -->
```
Phase 0: Research    → Dependencies, impact analysis, test plan
Phase 1+: Implement  → Code + tests
Phase N: Audit       → gate-runner.sh wo_exit
Phase N+1: Commit    → Only if gates pass
```

### Single Tracker
All WO status tracked in `docs/planning/WO-INDEX.md` (one file, no parity checking).

